Then $\cos \theta = \sqrt{1 - x^2}$ and $\cos \phi = \sqrt{1 - (1 - x)^2} = \sqrt{2x - x^2}.$  Also, $\arccos x = \frac{\pi}{2} - \theta.$  Hence,
\[\theta + \phi = \frac{\pi}{2} - \theta.\]Then $\theta = \frac{\pi}{4}$ and $\phi = \frac{\pi}{4} - \arcsin x.$  Hence,
\[\arcsin x = \frac{\pi}{4} - \phi = \frac{\pi}{4} - \left( \frac{\pi}{4} - \arcsin x \right) = \arcsin x,\]so $\arcsin x = \boxed{\frac{\pi}{4}}.$
